that you have a system in place so

3
00:00:10.381 --> 00:00:12.900
that they can quickly get into the flow.

4
00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:16.480
This is a way to waste a lot of time if
there's not a good system for them to

5
00:00:16.480 --> 00:00:19.950
get all of the support and the help that
they need to get up and running as quickly

6
00:00:19.950 --> 00:00:23.880
as possible and really start helping
your organization as fast as they can.

7
00:00:23.880 --> 00:00:26.830
So the onboarding process usually
starts with an initial meeting.

8
00:00:26.830 --> 00:00:29.550
So this should be with
whoever their manager is.

9
00:00:29.550 --> 00:00:33.620
And they should go over an overview of
their position, what the expectations are.

10
00:00:33.620 --> 00:00:37.520
In particular, what are the projects
that you'd like to have them complete,

11
00:00:37.520 --> 00:00:40.680
who they're supposed to interact with and
at what time scale.

12
00:00:40.680 --> 00:00:44.260
And are you gonna start those
interactions, or do they need to go and

13
00:00:44.260 --> 00:00:46.320
