00:02:34.748 --> 00:02:37.640
with, make sure that you do
a direct introduction of them.

51
00:02:37.640 --> 00:02:41.230
So that everyone knows the new person
is here, the new data scientist, or

52
00:02:41.230 --> 00:02:43.370
data engineer,
who they're gonna be interacting with,

53
00:02:43.370 --> 00:02:47.000
how to contact those people,
how you want that process to work.

54
00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:50.630
If you sort of initiate that yourself,
then it makes it a little bit smoother for

55
00:02:50.630 --> 00:02:52.520
them to know where to
go in the organization,

56
00:02:52.520 --> 00:02:55.200
if that's all sort of outlined
right from the beginning.

57
00:02:55.200 --> 00:02:56.790
Right from the get go.

58
00:02:56.790 --> 00:03:00.770
Another thing that all data scientists or
data engineers will need is equipment and

59
00:03:00.770 --> 00:03:01.890
communications.

